OL,6,FThe case for the violin was sold at
OL,7,Fthe same auction as the pocket watch
OL,8,Fat Henry Aldridge & Son on Saturday
OL,9,Ffor #360,000.
OL,11,FAuctioneer Andrew Aldridge told the PA
OL,12,Fnews agency that the prices fetched by
OL,13,Fthe Titanic memorabilia at the sale
OL,14,Fwere "absolutely incredible".
OL,16,FHe said: "They reflect not only the
OL,17,Fimportance of the artefacts themselves
OL,18,Fand their rarity but they also show
OL,19,Fthe enduring appeal and fascination
OL,20,Fwith the Titanic story.
